# Original data description:


- temperature and salinity

	## WOA2013

	## downloaded original from...

	## locally mirrored: 
 	/g/data1/v45/akm157/data/WOA13v2

- temperature and current in the Pacific Ocean
	
	## meanfit_m.cdf
	2017-11-14 download from https://floats.pmel.noaa.gov/gregory-c-johnson-home-page, "Equatorial Pacific Mean CTD/ADCP Sections in NetCDF from Johnson et al. (2002)."

- Global current

	## drifter_annualmeans.nc

	2017-11-14 download from http://www.aoml.noaa.gov/phod/dac/dac_meanvel.php, "A drifter-derived monthly climatology of global near-surface currents"

        resolution: 1440x632 
	NOTE: dimension order: longitude, latitude, Longitude from -179.875-179.875

        Reference:
	Laurindo, L., A. Mariano, and R. Lumpkin, 2017: An improved near-surface velocity climatology for the global ocean from drifter observations Deep-Sea Res. I, 124, pp.73-92, doi:10.1016/j.dsr.2017.04.009 .

	More data (monthly mean) can be downloaded from ftp://ftp.aoml.noaa.gov/phod/pub/lumpkin/drifter_climatology. 

- MLD
	## mld_DR003_c1m_reg2.0.nc  

        2017-10-24 download from http://www.ifremer.fr/cerweb/deboyer/mld/Surface_Mixed_Layer_Depth.php

	## ml_MLD_CLIM_ann.nc (processing the annual mean data)
	
        2017-11-03 download from ftp://ftp2.jamstec.go.jp/pub/argo/MILA_GPV/monthly/mld/2x2/, more data can be downloaded (month and 10days).

        For more information, visit http://www.jamstec.go.jp/ARGO/argo_web/ancient/MILAGPV/index_e.html

- SSH
 
	## zos_AVISO_L4_199210-201012.nc 
	
	2017-10-24 download from ftp://podaac-ftp.jpl.nasa.gov/allData/aviso/L4/dynamic_topo_1deg_1mo, For more information, visit https://podaac.jpl.nasa.gov/dataset/AVISO_L4_DYN_TOPO_1DEG_1MO 
        

	
